Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.83,0:03:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.31,0:03:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long heard of Zǐjìng speak of your talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.08,0:03:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm honored to meet you today and wanted to ask your advice face to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:03.76,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,500,3300,4000)\pos(1227.121,752.8)}Zhūgě Liàng\NStyled: Kǒngmíng
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.85,0:04:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I am only of modest ability, \Nplease forgive my boorishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.56,0:04:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you, sir, have been assisting \NLiú of Yù-Province, battling Cáo Cāo at Xinye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.30,0:04:08.76,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1179.36,711.583)}Sūn Quán \NStyled: Zhòngmóu
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.13,0:04:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely you must know of Cáo Cāo's actual strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.27,0:04:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you not know how many troops the Cao army has altogether?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.91,0:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,With cavalry, infantry, and naval troops combined: more than a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.15,0:04:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's not a trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is no trick. Cáo Cāo initially had 200,000 Qing-Province troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.93,0:04:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He gained 500,000 or 600,000 by defeating Yuan Shao —
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,, — 300,000 or 400,000 via recruiting in the Central Plains —
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,, — and 200,000 and 300,000 via surrendered soldiers from Jing Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Calculating from this, it is no less than a million and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.04,0:05:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I only said a million so as not to scare everyone here at Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.82,0:05:01.04,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(208,752)}Huáng Gài \NStyled: Gōngfù
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.18,0:05:08.18,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(252,714)}Lǔ Sù \NStyled: Zǐjìng
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.80,0:05:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How many generals are under Cáo Cāo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.20,0:05:23.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Counting crafty, sharp advisors, \Nand capable, veteran officers?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.78,0:05:25.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Hardly less than one or two thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,After taking Jīng Province, does Cáo Cāo have other plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.75,0:05:35.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why else, other than to take Jiangdong —
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.50,0:05:38.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— is he constructing defenses along the river and preparing warships?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Since he indeed wants to conquer us —
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.99,0:05:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,, — War, or peace? \NWhy not, sir, decide this for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.77,0:05:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Chaos abounds in the world, \Nand lords contest for their place —
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.40,0:06:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And today's Cáo Cāo's reputation is mighty and his strength seems invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.98,0:06:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Although Lord Líu Bèi continues to struggle, he's been defeated repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.88,0:06:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I would suggest the General to measure first  —
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:16.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — If with the peoples of Wú and Yue, you can contend with Cáo Cāo  —
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.25,0:06:18.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — then might as well break off ties now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.36,0:06:22.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If you feel your foundations are weak  —
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.64,0:06:26.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — Why not kneel to his rule and avoid slaughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.90,0:06:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, I said this to the men of Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.94,0:06:36.64,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(248,728)}Zhāng Zhāo\NStyled: Zǐbù
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.27,0:06:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone seems quite willing to surrender to Cáo Cāo,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.18,0:06:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,General, why not follow Heaven's will and the people's wishes, and seek peace and ease?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.37,0:07:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is indeed as you say, why does Líu Xuande not surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.22,0:07:11.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,In history, when Qí-State's Tían Hēng  —
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.31,0:07:17.48,Note (Potential style?),NTP,0,0,0,,Note: Tían Hēng was one of many leaders of the rebellions against the late \NQin Dynasty in 209-207 BCE, and was a member of the Qí-State's royal family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.08,0:07:14.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,  — led five hundred warriors to an island, and swore never to surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.31,0:07:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All five hundred heroically kept their oaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.22,0:07:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Uncle Líu is of imperial lineage!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His talent is unparalleled, he is admired by all. If he is defeated, then it is the will of Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:29.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Rather be as Tían Hēng and break like jade —
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.18,0:07:32.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — so how could he kneel and beg, \Nand go to serve the nation's villain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, that was far too wanton!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.38,0:07:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I admonished you many times, but you refused to listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.75,0:07:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, if my lord was not magnanimous, he would surely chastise you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:08:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words, sir, are entirely too contemptuous of my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.73,0:08:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does Sun Zhongmou have such little forbearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I have the plan to defeat Cáo Cāo, \Nhe refused to ask, so why should I tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If your plan to defeat Cáo Cāo is so good, then I earnestly ask you to tell me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.78,0:08:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In my view, Cáo Cāo's million-man army —
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.85,0:08:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,— is but a horde of ants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.89,0:08:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I need but wave my hand, and the million Cáo troops are but dust and powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.26,0:08:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please wait a moment— let me bring my lord to hear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Libelous, that Kongming!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.44,0:08:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, I too have thus criticized Kǒngmíng—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:08:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,— yet he laughed sire as shallow-minded in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.65,0:09:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that Kǒngmíng already has a plan to defeat Cáo Cāo in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He would not say this lightly, so my lord, why not seek to learn this from him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.14,0:09:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So Kǒngmíng already has a strategy, \Nand purposefully used wordplay to goad me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.91,0:09:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shallow-minded, and nearly put great matters at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.62,0:09:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us go!  My lord, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.86,0:09:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Sleeping Dragon  —
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.09,0:09:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My words were offensive, may the general please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.17,0:09:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Servants!  Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.62,0:09:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare a banquet in the rear hall, to host the Sleeping Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.27,0:09:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes sir!\N-Sir, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.18,0:09:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Please
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.29,0:11:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, does sir also enjoy listening to music?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.03,0:11:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Sleeping Dragon is talented in old musics.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.94,0:11:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When in Longzhong, he was skilled in playing the {\i1}Liángfùyín{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.90,0:11:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah no, I merely enjoy music.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.81,0:11:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, sir, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.32,0:11:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Pity that Gōngjǐng is not with us —
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.09,0:11:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,— else, Sir Sleeping Dragon would have met a kindred spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:12:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long heard of his charms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the children's songs of Jiangdong say thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.94,0:12:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16.318}{\i1}'If the song has err, Zhōu-láng can take care.'{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.14,0:12:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But, pray tell, where is Gōngjǐng now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.64,0:12:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I ordered him to Lake Fanyang, to conduct naval exercises.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.05,0:12:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please —
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.66,0:12:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,At the start of all this, many men rose and each dominated a region.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.57,0:12:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, Yuan Shao, Yuan Shu, Lu Bu, Líu Biao and others, have all perished—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.47,0:12:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Only me, Liu of Yu-Province, and Cáo Cāo remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.18,0:12:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot cede all the lands of Wú to another—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:13:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,— But since Líu Bèi was just recently defeated, how could he resist Cáo Cāo?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.23,0:13:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Though my lord is defeated, Guan Yunchang still leads ten thousand elite troops—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.99,0:13:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,— While Líu Qi also has ten thousand soldiers at Jiangxia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.41,0:13:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As well , Cáo Cāos's army, having marched south over such long distances, are extremely exhausted—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:22.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Not long before, while pursuing my lord—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.02,0:13:26.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— His light cavalry ran 300{\i1}li {\i0}in a single day and night —
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.46,0:13:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,— It's like they say: a bolt at the end of a strong crossbow's range cannot pierce even rough fabric.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, northern troops are unskilled at naval combat—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,— while the people of Jing-Province are unwilling to serve Cáo Cāo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.24,0:13:40.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If the General and my lord could unite in purpose —
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.10,0:13:42.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— then Cáo Cāo will surely be defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.43,0:13:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If Cáo Cāo is beaten, then he will return north.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With the waxing might of Jing-Province and Eastern Wú —
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,— we can stand as the legs of a crucible,\N in a balance of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.35,0:14:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Victory or defeat depends on this battle. May the General decide!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.93,0:14:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words are enlightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.97,0:14:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have decided, and will hesitate no longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.97,0:14:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, come, drink a few more cups!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.05,0:14:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I have not ate like this for many days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.54,0:14:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord —
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord has fallen for Kǒngmíng's plot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.18,0:15:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.45,0:15:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you battle Cáo Cāo, my lord, how do you think you compare to Yuan Shao?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.13,0:15:18.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Back then Cáo Cāo's army was small and his generals few,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.07,0:15:21.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,but he could still wipe out Yuan Shao in one fell swoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.12,0:15:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, today he wields an army of a million to march southward —
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.54,0:15:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,, — how could you take your enemy so lightly?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.74,0:15:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.17,0:15:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, if you listen to the words of Zhuge Liang, and rashly march out —
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.98,0:15:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,, — then it's as if you are putting out a fire while carrying dry twigs on your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.82,0:15:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-Indeed, indeed! \N-Lord must reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.14,0:16:02.06,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1224,748)}Gù Yōng \NStyled: Yuántàn
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.27,0:16:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Líu Bèi is in defeat and only seeks to borrow the armies of Jiangdong to stop Cáo Cāo's forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.68,0:16:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How could my lord bear to be used by others?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.76,0:16:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.13,0:17:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.74,0:17:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, you are sagacious,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.60,0:17:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,— so do not be shaken by those coward gentry who fear death and seek to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.41,0:17:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If my lord hesitates like so, you will used by others
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.47,0:17:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Please retire, and let me think on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.74,0:17:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.87,0:18:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, the State Mother has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.27,0:18:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.11,0:19:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, everything is peaceful here, \Nand you need not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.06,0:19:33.06,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1160,548)}State Mother Wú
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Son, I have heard you do not eat nor drink, and cannot sleep. Is there something troubling you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.56,0:19:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo armies press upon my borders, and seek to devour our Eastern Wú.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My military and civil officials cannot decide between peace or war, and debate endlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I had thought to fight, but I fear we are outnumbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.10,0:19:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I surrender, then I fear that Cáo Cāo would not tolerate my survival, and thus I cannot decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still remember their last words?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,'In internal matters, inquire Zhāng Zhāo' —
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,— 'In external matters, inquire Zhōu Yú!'
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.16,0:20:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not invite Zhōu Yú here and ask him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.33,0:20:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, mother! In my bustling, I had forgotten his words.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.73,0:20:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Zhongmou, no matter how important the matter, your health is vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.54,0:20:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If my son ever fell to misfortune —
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.11,0:20:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how could I face our family who have passed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.61,0:20:37.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Mother, please be at ease, I will send someone to Fanyang —
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.65,0:20:39.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— and invite Gōngjǐng back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:21:00.36,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,200,2300,2650)\pos(1186.648,736)}Zhōu Yú \NStyled: Gōngjǐn
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.78,0:21:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-My husband!\N-My wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.32,0:21:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.56,0:21:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The lord had just sent someone here, order you to return quickly—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.03,0:21:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,— but you have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.93,0:21:25.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,My dear, Cáo Cāo's army is upon our borders —
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:29.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— but sire has not yet decided between peace and war, so I cannot be at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.97,0:21:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear, you must be tired from the long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.49,0:21:37.45,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1198,722)}Xiǎo Qiáo
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.11,0:21:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear wife, when I rushed back here overnight, all I could think about was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.45,0:21:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You just exaggerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.92,0:21:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As your wife, how could I not know my husband's nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.32,0:21:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For state matters and military duty, you could forget to eat and sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.60,0:21:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How can there be time for his family?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.93,0:22:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Zhang Zhao is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.51,0:22:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You've just come back, and we can't even have a moment of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.15,0:22:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right then, tell them to go back, I am going to spend tonight with my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.99,0:22:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, go then, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.64,0:22:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.78,0:22:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.14,0:22:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.02,0:22:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.63,0:23:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, you talk first.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.33,0:23:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.30,0:23:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Zibu, if you have something to say, please say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.70,0:23:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, do you know of Jiangdong's current plight?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.41,0:23:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.58,0:23:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo has a million men, assembled upon the great river.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.02,0:23:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,His war declaration arrived yesterday, inviting our lord to hunt with him at Jiangxia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.22,0:23:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,While he does mean to devour us, \Nhe has not revealed the intention —
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.63,0:23:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will persuade our lord to surrender tomorrow, to prevent calamity from coming to Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.98,0:23:58.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,But we didn't think Lu Zijing would bring \NLíu Bèi's strategist Zhuge Liang from Jiangxia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.42,0:24:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They want revenge on Cao army, so purposely used his words to goad my lord
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.29,0:24:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But Zijing... is blind and stubborn. We wish the Grand Marshal would make his decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.47,0:24:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everyone here favor surrendering?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.90,0:24:22.76,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(199.277,742)}Bù Zhì\NStyled: Zǐshān
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.71,0:24:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All of our opinions are the same as Zibu's.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.85,0:24:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long favored surrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.19,0:24:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please, go back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.19,0:24:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When meeting our lord tomorrow morning, I will indeed have something to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.16,0:24:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.76,0:24:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.24,0:24:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Gōngjǐng, do the gentry favor fighting or surrendering?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.31,0:25:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,According to your opinion, my dear, should we fight or surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.78,0:25:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our lord dominates Jiangdong, and has been established for three generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.33,0:25:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,With the river to the north, and fertile lands to the South,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.77,0:25:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Virtuous lords above, and famed generals below.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.60,0:25:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How could we kneel before the tyrant of the Hàn?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.58,0:25:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheng Pu and other generals have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.80,0:25:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-Grand Marshal.    \N-Senior General Huang.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.40,0:25:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Senior General Cheng
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.87,0:25:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.18,0:26:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.98,0:26:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, did you know that the southlands are soon to belong to another?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.52,0:26:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.06,0:26:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.92,0:26:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,— We have built our realm with General Sun —
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.48,0:26:24.44,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,390,3600,4000)\pos(266.091,723.364)}Chéng Pǔ\NStyled: Démóu
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.93,0:26:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,— and fought hundreds of battles large and small to have the six commanderies of Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.20,0:26:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, a group of advisors dare to persuade our lord to surrender to Cáo.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.77,0:26:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is shameful! Despicable!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.84,0:26:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We would rather die than surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.88,0:26:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,May the general persuade our lord to plan decisively and muster the armies —
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.98,0:26:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,— so we can do our duty unto death!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.47,0:27:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, do you all agree on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.44,0:27:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We would rather die than surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.74,0:27:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Huang Gai can lose my head, but I swear to never kneel and surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.18,0:27:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.95,0:27:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking forward to fight Cáo Cāo, how could I kneel and surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.13,0:27:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Generals, please go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.59,0:27:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait until I have met our lord tomorrow, and I will have an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.77,0:27:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.64,0:27:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.31,0:27:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.65,0:27:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal. My brother Zhuge Liang has arrived from Jiangxia as envoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.02,0:27:53.88,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,390,3200,3700)\pos(1172,760)}Zhūgě Jǐn \NStyled: Zǐyú
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.68,0:27:56.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He says Líu Bèi wishes to ally with Eastern Wú, to defeat Cáo Cāo together.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.45,0:27:59.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,The officials have not come to a decision —
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.56,0:28:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,— but because my brother is \Nthe envoy, I dared not say much —
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.06,0:28:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,, — and waited for Grand-Marshal to decide on this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.17,0:28:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your opinion on this, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.45,0:28:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who surrender find safety.  \NThose who fight... May not survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.49,0:28:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I have made my own decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.57,0:28:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Officials, generals.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.77,0:28:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already chosen between war and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.57,0:28:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I will discuss this with our lord tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.78,0:28:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.43,0:29:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.90,0:29:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear, I have already seen off the military and civil officials  —
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.30,0:29:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,, —  so no one else will disturb us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.14,0:29:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.98,0:29:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, Lu Su has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.25,0:29:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,See?  Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.02,0:29:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The nation is in crisis, \Nand yet you are so relaxed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.76,0:29:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Zijing, you need not say more. Just invite Sir Kǒngmíng here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.59,0:29:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, I will let this fine couple reunite for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.65,0:30:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The strings on the {\i1}qin{\i0}-zither have been neglected thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.30,0:30:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear, I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.83,0:31:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand-Marshal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.12,0:31:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.19,0:31:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.16,0:31:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Marshal,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.53,0:32:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now Cáo Cāo's army is gathered on \Nthe river, sire cannot decide at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.47,0:32:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure what the Marshal's opinion is?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.70,0:32:18.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo seized the emperor and commands the lords —
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.59,0:32:21.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,His strength is great \Nand his might cannot be stopped,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.78,0:32:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighting will lead to defeat, while surrendering would lead to safety. I've already made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.22,0:32:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow when I meet with the lord, envoys shall be sent to offer surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.14,0:32:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Kǒngmíng, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.54,0:32:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.58,0:32:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You speak wrongly, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.84,0:32:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The realm of Jiangdong was built over three generations, how could it be ceded to another?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.28,0:32:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the very fate of the nation is in just the General's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.02,0:32:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you listen to the discourse of cowards?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.50,0:33:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Countless lives reside in the six commanderies of the southlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.30,0:33:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If war breaks out, then the people will fall to deprivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.10,0:33:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I propose war, then would not all the young and old of the southlands heap blame upon me?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.28,0:33:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong. With the general's heroism, \Nand the natural barriers of Eastern Wú —
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.55,0:33:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,— Cáo Cāo may not get his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.89,0:33:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does sir laugh so?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.09,0:33:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I laugh because Zijing refuses to see the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.03,0:33:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does sir laugh at me also?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.80,0:33:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Gōngjǐn's idea to surrender to Cáo Cāo is indeed reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.68,0:33:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo is a master of war, unrivalled in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.58,0:34:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the many heroes who contested him, almost all have perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.79,0:34:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Liu of Yu-Province fails to understand this, and fights back—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.08,0:34:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,— only to fall to routing to Jiangxia, barely alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.60,0:34:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Should the general decide to surrender to Cao.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.00,0:34:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You protect your family on one hand, \Nand on the other can preserve your riches and luxury.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.04,0:34:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord's fate is up to heaven, do we really need to pity him?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.98,0:34:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, do you want my lord to kneel before the nation's villain?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.52,0:34:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not worry, Zijing, I have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.95,0:34:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We need neither cede our territory, \Nnor offer our seals and declare servitude —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.03,0:34:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—in order to drive back Cáo Cāo's million strong host.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.06,0:34:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What brilliant plan do you have, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.54,0:34:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}You merely need to send a single messenger to ferry two persons across the river —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.28,0:35:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}If Cáo Cāo can have these two, his hordes will furl their banners, and retire from the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.88,0:35:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}The Southland's parting with these two would be no more than a leaf from a tree —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.38,0:35:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}—or a grain of millet from a granary.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.53,0:35:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Who are these two persons?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.54,0:35:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}When I was in Longzhong—
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.78,0:35:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}—I heard that Cáo Cāo was building a new pavilion near River Zhang.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.28,0:35:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}It was to be named {\i1}'the Bronze Sparrow Terrace'.{\i0} \NA magnificent edifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.28,0:35:35.48,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,AKA. Tóngquètái (铜雀台)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.21,0:35:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}He sought far and wide for beautiful women to fill its chambers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.92,0:35:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}We know Cáo Cāo as a lecherous man. He has heard patriarch Qiao of Jiangdong has two daughters —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.14,0:35:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Eldest called 	"Dà Qiáo", younger called "Xiǎo Qiáo".
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.20,0:35:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}— beauties who make birds alight and fishes drown, abash the very blossoms and outshine the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.90,0:36:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Cáo Cāo has once vowed —
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.71,0:36:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}— to have only two dreams; 'To sweep the realm and see the imperial throne in peace —
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.85,0:36:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}—and the sight of those two women\Non the Bronze Sparrow Terraces —
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.22,0:36:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}— and retire in pleasure, and die without regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.39,0:36:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}His million-fold host that threatens Jiangnan, has for its real aim these two women.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.04,0:36:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Why not seek the patriarch Qiao and his daughers with gold, and exchange them over the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Once has these two, he will be content and return to the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.78,0:36:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}What proof do you have for Cáo Cāo desiring the two Qiaos?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.39,0:37:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Cáo Cāo has a son, {\i1}Cáo Zhí{\i0}, styled {\i1}Zǐjiàn{\i0}.\NA prodigy and a writer of great genius —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.67,0:37:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}At the command of his father wrote a poem\N{\i1}‘An Ode to the Bronze Sparrow Terrace' —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.87,0:37:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Its theme the fitness of his house for sovereignty and his possession of the Two Qiaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.48,0:37:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Can sir recite this poem?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.22,0:37:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16} I admired the gorgeous language of this poem, thus I committed it to memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.36,0:37:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}May I request a recitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.20,0:37:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}I will try.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.54,0:37:48.42,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Ode to the Bronze Sparrow Terrace ("铜雀台赋")\Nby Cáo Zhí, edited by Luó Guànzhōng
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.54,0:37:45.57,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Beside His Esteemed steps I do rejoice so —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.34,0:37:48.51,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}mounting storied towers in delight —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.92,0:37:56.11,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Peering down on River Zhang's ever-flow —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.22,0:38:00.69,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}whence fruits abundant promise glory —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.36,0:38:05.49,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Aloft rises twin towers either flank —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.00,0:38:09.72,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}one Jade Dragon, and a Phoenix Gold —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.74,0:38:15.23,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}With 'Two Qiaos' holding from Southeast so —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.74,0:38:19.22,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Note: The surname "Qiáo" sounds similar to the word for bridge, so Cao Cao's words were heard differently by Zhou Yu.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.77,0:38:18.53,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}would joys last dawn to dusk evermore  —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.18,0:38:23.57,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Look upon the royal city's beauty —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.88,0:38:27.54,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}behold the clouds lie floating beneath —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.42,0:38:31.55,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Oh rest, Oh grace! —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.36,0:38:36.53,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}To only be bound by heaven and earth —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.89,0:38:40.22,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}bright as the glory of sun and moon —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.76,0:38:43.80,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Ever honored and ever enduring —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.47,0:38:49.13,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}age immortal as the Father-East —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.61,0:38:55.68,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}May I wish this tower ever standing —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.65,0:39:00.44,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}for joys of ages never failing!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.25,0:39:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}That bastard Cao dares to mock me!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.96,0:39:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Recall when the Son of Heaven granted a princess of Hàn to wed with Xiongnu for peace—
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.33,0:39:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Why should we miss for two women of the crowd?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.60,0:39:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Sir might not be aware—
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.20,0:39:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Da Qiao was the wife of my former lord Sūn Bófú, and Xiao Qiao- !
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.81,0:39:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Xiao Qiao is Grand Marshal's very own wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.42,0:39:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I really did not know!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.62,0:39:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My words were poor, it's a crime worthy of death! Please forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.04,0:39:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.97,0:39:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear this world cannot hold both Cáo Cāo and I!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.28,0:40:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, though this is infuriating, please think carefully before proceeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.10,0:40:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sun Bofu and I have such a deep friendship —
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.83,0:40:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,— And now upon me is great responsibility for the state —
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.91,0:40:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,— so how could I kneel before Cáo Cāo?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.60,0:40:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To speak frankly, I was merely testing you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.68,0:40:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the moment I left Fanyang, I had already made up my mind to campaign against Cáo Cāo.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.12,0:40:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the path might be filled with blades, I will not waver.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.69,0:40:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,May sir lend me his strength, so we may break Cáo Cāo together.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.67,0:41:00.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If you deem me worthy, I wish to aid you with to my utmost —
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.61,0:41:03.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— and will be as the Grand Marshal commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.64,0:41:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.35,0:41:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow we will go and see our lord, and discuss the matter of raising an army!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.76,0:41:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.33,0:41:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I have heard all of Kǒngmíng's words back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.87,0:42:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Cáo Cāo did not raise his armies specifically for us —
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.90,0:42:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If the southern lands fall, then I fear—
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.00,0:42:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and our children will fall into the hands of the Cáo villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.24,0:42:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife, please don't worry, I will convince my Lord to fight Cáo Cāo
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.25,0:42:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the children asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.50,0:42:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They are asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.88,0:42:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For a great general, yet such a heart for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.26,0:43:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Men are not wood or grass, \Nhow could I be heartless?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.93,0:43:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be giving orders from the terrace, spurring the horses and armies.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.83,0:43:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Above I can return my lord's deep generosity —
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.34,0:43:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,— Below I can bring glory for my wife and family, my life's wishes fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.01,0:43:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I have always loved your talent —
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.62,0:43:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,— and I wish for you to build unparalleled achievements—
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.39,0:43:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,— something that I and the children can feel pride for as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.50,0:43:45.23,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Zhuge Liang, in order to unite with Wú to resist Cáo, using his ingenuity—
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.84,0:43:51.00,Thinking,NTP,0,0,0,,— cleverly changed the meaning of the "Two Qiáos" in the "Ode to the Bronze Sparrow Terrace."—
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.84,0:43:53.84,Thinking,,0,0,0,,—thus enraging Zhōu Yú to act —
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.15,0:44:00.25,Thinking,,0,0,0,,— and revealing his hidden will to challenge Cáo Cāo to the death.
